=begin

gemguard

       author: Mystienne
         game: gs
      version: 0.18.7
        build: 07032026.23
         tags: gems, selling, purify, orb-testing, chrisms, gemcutters
     required: Lich >= 5.11.0
        email: Mystienne@mystienne.com
      discord: Mystienne

GemGuard helps players review gems before selling them.
It opens your chosen gem containers, shows what will sell and what will be kept,
appraises gems, and sells approved gems one at a time.

It can keep protected gem names, marked gems, chrisms, and pure orbs out of the
sell list. Bards can also use it to purify gems and sort pure orbs. It can look
for chrisms and move them into a saved chrism container. It can save lapidary
box setup details and cut selected gems when a matching pattern is saved.

Always review the sell list before pressing Sell Approved.

=end

require 'fileutils'
require 'timeout'
require 'yaml'

# GemGuard manages gem review, selling, protection, and profession-specific gem
# workflows for one character at a time. The methods in this namespace send game
# commands, update per-character YAML files, and manage GTK windows.
module GemGuard
  extend self

