  output = "\n"
  output.concat "#{gemguard_inline_preset('thought', 'gemguard changelog:')}\n"
  output.concat "\n"
  output.concat "#{gemguard_inline_preset('thought', '07-03-2026')}\n"
  output.concat '   0.18.7 - fix(gemcutter): Saved chrism strength and fullness when LOOK proves a gem is a chrism, added protected-list exceptions so broad names like sapphire can stay protected while exact names like blue sapphire can be allowed to sell, made the X and Close button close the GTK window immediately like Highlight Manager and stop GemGuard too, added lapidary Cut Selected buttons on the Review and Gemcutter tabs that cut selected Review gems with saved patterns, switches to the Gemcutter tab when Review Cut Selected starts, makes the visible Gemcutter button change to Stop when cutting is started from Review, added a saved lapidary box container so cutting can get the box directly, waits for the quoted visible panel design before deciding whether to TURN, handles trailing punctuation in visible lapidary pattern text, uses TURN and exact visible box panel text to set lapidary designs because WHISPER can report success without changing the panel, refuses to cut when the requested pattern cannot be confirmed, waits for full container listings before using cached contents, uses command results instead of stale hand cache when holding gems for cutting, added optional Gemcutter debug logging with version and build stamps, shows failed cut reasons and estimated time remaining in the Gemcutter status, waits for physical cutter roundtime before putting the gem away, uses GameObj hand state to avoid empty-hand STOW spam, and fixed startup container refresh when the Gemcutter tab is still being built.' + "\n"
  output.concat "\n"
  output.concat "#{gemguard_inline_preset('thought', '07-02-2026')}\n"
  output.concat '   0.13.0 - feat(gemcutter): Made Gemcutter pattern choices dropdowns that use saved lapidary designs, support any number of designs from the analyzed tool, keep already-saved pattern choices available, and refresh choices after Analyze Box saves designs.' + "\n"
  output.concat "\n"
